<TITLE> UZ chairman arrested for breaking PM's photo </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dinajpur, Apr 30 (bdnews24.com)Biral upazila chairman Mokarram Hossain Moka was arrested on Friday on charges of shattering prime minister Sheikh Hasina's portrait. Upazila Awami League president Ishaque Ali Sarkar filed the case under the Speedy Trial Act on Thursday night, Biral police chief Akmal Hossain told journalists on Friday. The chairman was detained from his house at around 3am, the police officer said. Mokarram allegedly misbehaved with Upazila Nirbahi officer (UNO) AKM Azadur Rahman before breaking the photo on Thursday noon. The officials of upazila administration did not join in their work in protest against the incident on Thursday. But the upazila chairman claimed that he had not broken the prime minister's photo. UNO Azadur Rahman complained to journalists that Mokarram had mistreated him and broken the photo. He said the upazila chairman had asked for an old jeep of the upazila Parishad. The UNO asked the chairman to apply for the vehicle and wait for written approval on Wednesday. bd
